Center: OECD/NEA Nuclear Data Bank, Boulogne-Billancourt, France
title: -Neutron Capture Measurements and Resonance Parameters of Mo-Isotopes.-

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Nuclear Physics, Section A, Vol.104, p.513 (1967)

x4freetext: MERCURY COOLED URANIUM TARGET, PULSED SOURCE
TIME OF FLIGHT, FLIGHT PATH = 60 M,
NOMINAL RESOLUTION VARIED BETWEEN 1.5 NSEC/M AND
THE NEUTRON ENERGY SPECTRUM WAS MEASURED
WITH A B-10 SLAB VIEWED BY A NAI CRYSTAL.
.ABSOLUTE CALIBRATION OF NEUTRON FLUX TIMES DETECTOR
EFFICIENCY WAS OBTAINED BY THE BLACK RESONANCE
TECHNIQUE, IN 5.2, 16.3 AND 51.4 EV RESONANCES IN AG.
AREA ANALYSIS PROGRAM BY FROHNER, HADDAD,
RESONANCE AREA ANALYSIS YIELDS G*GAMMA(N) FOR SMALL
RESONANCES OR G*GAMMA(G) FOR LARGE ONES.
